A nice work in progress parc , large for Paris, on the minimalist and modern side. Great for kids, they have free range animals roaming the south part of the parc, artists residency and a small school. A dog parc is offered and it‚Äôs great for running.

This area has traditionally been a run down, poor neighborhood, surrounded by low income housing high rises and with rising local crime, most recently crack dealing. There is a lot of this in this new garden, with people shooting up and smoking base, with not a whole lot of police presence. Quite a shame as new residents, drawn by cheaper rents and new nicely designed social housing units, have nowhere to walk their children or dogs because the garden has just become scummy.Hopefully the local authorities will do something about this one day and not just create a new park for photo opportunities and then just leave it to disintegrate and become dangerous.
